Subject: Re: [T2] Led tailights for '74 Westy

On Fri, 2 Jan 2009, David Schwarze wrote:

> George Lyle wrote:
> > This seems to be a common occurance with the "bulb replacement" type
> > units.  You just can't replace a small brilliant bulb with an array of
> > LEDs and expect it to work properly with the lens and reflector.
>
> I think it could have worked if the LEDs had not all been mounted in the
> same plane.

I found a package that seems to work.

> > What I've been thinking of doing is getting raw LEDs and installing them
> > in holes drilled in the perimeter of the stock taillight lens of my '71.
> > These would be wired in parallel with the stock bulb.  That way you get
> > the advantages of the LEDs but retain the stock bulb which is needed
> > anyway to make the flasher work properly.

I'm not sure it will fit the smaller taillight housing, I have a 78
which has a larger housing and lens.

> Personally I am waiting for the double-superDOOPERbrightLEDs like the
> ones they have on cop cars to become available.  A few of those in a
> spray pattern ought to make an acceptable substitute for a stock bulb.

mine has 4 LED in a line and use one for tail lights and a second one
for brake lights.  I left the standard bulb for turn and backup lights
so it doesn't affect the blinkers.

